                <h1>Discover the Legacy of John D. Rockefeller</h1>
                <p>John D. Rockefeller was a pivotal figure in American industry, revolutionizing the oil industry in the 19th century. He founded the Standard Oil Company, which became a powerful monopoly. Known for his philanthropic efforts, he contributed vast sums to education, health, and scientific research, leaving a lasting legacy in both business and society.</p>
